               <p>11. 
               
                  <persName id="t17371012-8-defend105" type="defendantName">
                     Lydia 
                     Goodwin 
                  <interp inst="t17371012-8-defend105" type="surname" value="Goodwin"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17371012-8-defend105" type="given" value="Lydia"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17371012-8-defend105" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
               
            , was indicted for <rs id="t17371012-8-off40" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17371012-8-off40" type="offenceCategory" value="deception"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17371012-8-off40" type="offenceSubcategory" value="perjury"></interp>
               wilful and corrupt Perjury, in swearing before 
                     <persName id="t17371012-8-person106">
                        Peter 
                        Barton 
                     <interp inst="t17371012-8-person106" type="surname" value="Barton"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t17371012-8-person106" type="given" value="Peter"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t17371012-8-person106" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     </persName>
                  , Gent. of the Poultry Compter, that 
                     
                        <persName id="t17371012-8-victim108" type="victimName">
                           Catherine 
                           Hyam 
                        <interp inst="t17371012-8-victim108" type="surname" value="Hyam"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t17371012-8-victim108" type="given" value="Catherine"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t17371012-8-victim108" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t17371012-8-off40 t17371012-8-victim108"></join>
                     </persName>
                      
                   was indebted to her in the Sum of 21 l. and 15 s.
            </rs> 
                  <rs id="t17371012-8-cd41" type="crimeDate">April 4, 1735</rs>
                  <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t17371012-8-off40 t17371012-8-cd41"></join>.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t17371012-8-verdict42" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17371012-8-verdict42" type="verdictCategory" value="notGuilty"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17371012-8-verdict42" type="verdictSubcategory" value="fault"></interp>
               But there being a Defect in the Indictment, the Prisoner was acquitted
            </rs>.</p>
